org.jungrapht.visualization.layout.algorithms

Interface IterativeLayoutAlgorithm<V>

  • Type Parameters:
    V - the Vertex type
    All Superinterfaces:
    IterativeContext, LayoutAlgorithm<V>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractIterativeLayoutAlgorithm, AnimationLayoutAlgorithm, DAGLayoutAlgorithm, FRLayoutAlgorithm, ISOMLayoutAlgorithm, KKLayoutAlgorithm, KKLayoutAlgorithmWithDijkstra, SpringLayoutAlgorithm

    public interface IterativeLayoutAlgorithm<V>
extends LayoutAlgorithm<V>, IterativeContext
    A LayoutAlgorithm that may utilize a pre-relax phase, which is a loop of calls to step that occurr in the current thread instead of in a new Thread. The purpose of preRelax() is to rapidly reach an initial state before spawning a new Thread to perform a more lengthy relax operation.
